original_title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Pleasant View Street
text:
Metropolitan Avenue, north side, at and adjoining Pleasantview Street, showing at the right, in two views, the Kallenstrab house on the site of Mrs. Coe's house. The Fearless Hook and Ladder Co, No. 7, organized in 1870, adjoins the first mentioned house.

1922
Views 1 and 2

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

original_title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Pleasant View Street
text:
7219-7241 Metropolitan Avenue, north side, east of Pleasantview Street, showing in the foreground white Bldg., a part of the Cornish Country house of 1870. One Wackenhut built the addition. He still owns both houses. Eugene L. Armbruster states it is on the site of the Losee house. Fred Weiss' Hotel is in the center of the view.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

original_title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Pleasant View Street
text:
Metropolitan Avenue (old No. 2039) north side, west of Pleasantview Street (right, not shown) showing Mrs. Ways' house. A later owner was John Sutter. E.H. Girard known as "Old Florist Girard" was the occupant in 1923. This house is not Mrs. S. Ways' personal home of 1852 nor that of Chas. F. Way.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
